# Modal Organization

## Stack (do not replace ad hoc)

- **Context + mount point**: `src/app/(_home)/_context/Modal.tsx` exports `ModalProvider`, `Modal`, and `useModal`.
- **Root wiring**: `src/app/layout.tsx` wraps the app in `ModalProvider` and renders a single `<Modal />` after `{children}` (sibling to routes and shell).
- **Triggers**: `src/app/(_home)/_components/OpenModalComponents/` (`OpenModalButton`, `OpenModalTableCell`) call `setModalContent` / `setOnModalClose` from `useModal`.

## Provider behavior

- `ModalProvider` holds `modalRef`, `modalContent`, `setModalContent`, `setOnModalClose`, and `closeModal`.
- A trailing `<div ref={modalRef} />` is the portal target for `ReactDOM.createPortal`.
- `closeModal` clears content and runs the optional close callback once.

## Modal shell

- `Modal` portals when `modalRef.current` and `modalContent` are set.
- Overlay: `#modal` full-screen centered; `#modal-background` (`bg-modalBackground`) calls `closeModal` on click.
- Content shell: `#modal-content` uses theme tokens (`bg-screenWhite`, `border-primary`, `rounded-2xl`, `max-w-[90%]`). Put feature UI inside this by passing it as `modalContent`.

## Opening pattern (match OpenModalComponents)

1. Optionally `setOnModalClose(callback)` when the opener passes `onModalClose`.
2. `setModalContent(modalComponent)` with the React node to show.
3. Optionally run `onButtonClick` after scheduling content.

Use `OpenModalButton` / `OpenModalTableCell` instead of duplicating this logic unless a genuinely different trigger is required.

## Rules

- **One** global `<Modal />` in root layout; never mount a second portal tree for the same system.
- Any component calling `useModal` must render under `ModalProvider` (already satisfied by root layout).
- Pass **`modalComponent`** as JSX (e.g. `<CreateFooModal ... />`). Modal bodies that need hooks/forms should be Client Components themselves.
- Prefer colocating feature modals under the domain folder (e.g. `.../Modals/CreateX.tsx`).

## Anti-patterns

- Using `createPortal` elsewhere for the same UX instead of `useModal`.
- Nesting a second `ModalProvider`.
- Forgetting `onModalClose` registration order (set callback before `setModalContent` when using the OpenModal pattern).
